# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Adjustfile — Drift-tolerance + accessibility contract for nextgen-typing
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>
#
# Cumulative-drift catchment: tolerance bands + corrective actions.
# Authority: advisory (Yard) — continue-with-warnings; auto_fix where deterministic.
# Run with: adjust check
# Fix with: adjust fix (applies deterministic patches; advisory otherwise)
#
# Provenance: repo-true rewrite at the 2026-06-12 governance checkpoint.
# Carries the estate drift-tolerance shape PLUS the accessibility
# invariants ported from the former root ADJUST.contractile
# ("Accessibility & Digital Justice for Universal Software & Technology",
# WCAG 2.2 AA), removed by the estate-standardization merge.

@abstract:
Drift tolerances and corrective actions for nextgen-typing. Unlike
MUST (hard gate), ADJUST tracks cumulative drift against tolerance bands
and proposes corrective actions. Advisory — it warns and trends, it does
not block. The accessibility section is normative for any user-facing
output this repo produces (docs, CLI tooling, diagrams).
@end

## Documentation Drift

### readme-state-sync
- description: README.adoc, docs/ARCHITECTURE.adoc, docs/PIPELINE.adoc and 6a2/{STATE,META,ECOSYSTEM}.a2ml should agree
- tolerance: No contradictions between narrative docs and 6a2 metadata
- corrective: Run the periodic drift scan listed in 6a2/STATE.a2ml critical-next-actions
- severity: advisory

### pipeline-currency
- description: Pipeline docs should track constituent-repo reality (typell, typed-wasm, katagoria, tropical-resource-typing, protocol-squisher)
- tolerance: Status table in README matches constituent repos' actual state
- corrective: Refresh the README status table and ECOSYSTEM.a2ml
- severity: advisory

### placeholder-drift
- description: Remaining template placeholders should trend to zero
- tolerance: 0 {{PLACEHOLDER}} markers outside .machine_readable/ai/PLACEHOLDERS.adoc
- corrective: Fill per PLACEHOLDERS.adoc (just init or manual sed pass)
- severity: advisory
- notes: As of 2026-06-12 placeholders remain in .github/ community files, self-validating/ k9 templates, and QUICKSTART-MAINTAINER.adoc (tracked as OQ-002 in 6a2/STATE.a2ml)

## Structural Drift

### no-broken-symlinks
- description: No broken symbolic links in the tree
- tolerance: 0 broken symlinks
- corrective: Remove or re-point the broken link
- severity: advisory

### adoc-not-md
- description: Prose docs should prefer AsciiDoc
- tolerance: New prose docs are *.adoc
- corrective: Convert any new *.md to *.adoc
- severity: advisory

### spdx-header-consistency
- description: All files have correct SPDX headers (MPL-2.0 since 2026-05-22)
- tolerance: 0 files missing SPDX-License-Identifier
- corrective: Add SPDX headers to files that need them
- severity: advisory

## Accessibility — Visual (ported from root ADJUST.contractile, WCAG 2.2 AA)

### colour-contrast
- description: Colour contrast ratio >= 4.5:1 normal text, >= 3:1 large text; no information conveyed by colour alone; no flashing content (3 flashes/second max)
- tolerance: WCAG 2.2 AA
- corrective: Fix palette / add non-colour signal
- severity: advisory

### text-resizable
- description: Text resizable to 200% without loss of content or function; focus indicators visible on all interactive elements
- tolerance: WCAG 2.2 AA
- corrective: Use relative units; add focus styles
- severity: advisory

## Accessibility — Keyboard and Screen Reader

### keyboard-reachable
- description: All interactive elements reachable via keyboard; no keyboard traps; skip-navigation present; logical focus order
- tolerance: WCAG 2.2 AA
- corrective: Add tabindex/skip links; fix focus order
- severity: advisory

### screen-reader-support
- description: Meaningful alt text on images; labelled form inputs; ARIA landmarks; aria-live for dynamic updates; semantic HTML (no div soup)
- tolerance: WCAG 2.2 AA
- corrective: Add alt/labels/landmarks/semantics
- severity: advisory

## Accessibility — CLI/TUI and Documentation

### cli-not-colour-only
- description: CLI output must not rely solely on colour (use symbols: [OK] [FAIL]); TUI supports high-contrast mode; --help with plain-text output; plain-language error messages
- tolerance: 100% of CLI surfaces
- corrective: Add symbol prefixes and --help text
- severity: advisory

### docs-plain-language
- description: Docs use clear language, short sentences, logical structure; code examples commented; diagrams have text descriptions
- tolerance: All new docs
- corrective: Editorial pass
- severity: advisory

## Accessibility — Internationalisation

### i18n-ready
- description: User-facing strings externalisable; no hardcoded English in error messages; locale-aware date/time/number formats; RTL support where applicable; UTF-8 throughout
- tolerance: All user-facing surfaces
- corrective: Externalise strings; use message keys
- severity: advisory
- notes: Related ecosystem resources — standards/lol (multilingual NLP corpus) and polyglot-i18n (i18n framework + WASM translation engine)

## Enforcement (advisory layer)

- ci: accessibility linting rides quality.yml where user-facing output exists
- tool: axe-core or pa11y for automated checks on any web UI
- tool: CLI output inspected for colour-only signalling
- manual: screen reader pass before major releases
